---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
---

<PageLayout
  title={`About ${SITE.name}`}
  description={`${SITE.name} builds privacy-first browser tools for inspecting LLM requests and formatting Markdown, HTML, JSON and text diffs.`}
  h1={`About ${SITE.name}`}
  path="/about"
>
  <p>
    <strong>{SITE.name}</strong> is an independently maintained collection of private, browser-only
    developer tools. Its primary purpose is to make the exact request sent to an LLM readable: message
    roles, escaped prompt text, tool calls and nested JSON. The supporting Markdown, HTML, JSON and
    diff tools cover the formats developers usually inspect around that workflow.
  </p>

  <h2>What you can do here</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="/prompt">AI Prompt Formatter</a> — turn an escaped, single-line
      LLM prompt from your logs into a clean, color-coded conversation with
      system / user / assistant roles split apart and inline JSON pretty-printed.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/markdown">Markdown Formatter</a> — paste Markdown and get a live,
      clean HTML preview you can copy.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/html">HTML Viewer &amp; Formatter</a> — render HTML safely in a
      sandbox or beautify messy markup instantly.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/json/">JSON Formatter &amp; Validator</a> — validate strict JSON, locate syntax errors
      and create a readable or minified copy.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/diff/">Text Diff Checker</a> — compare request payloads, configuration and prose in
      split or unified views.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How the tools are built and checked</h2>
  <p>
    The site is a static Astro application deployed on Cloudflare Pages. Formatting happens in the
    browser with established libraries where appropriate. HTML previews are sanitized and rendered in
    an iframe with an empty sandbox, while Markdown disables raw HTML and sanitizes its rendered
    output. Production builds are verified before deployment, and guides are reviewed against the
    behavior of the live tools when their verified date changes.
  </p>
  <p>
    The source is available in the
    <a href="https://github.com/yangkaiHandsome/promt_formater" rel="noopener noreferrer">public GitHub repository</a>,
    so privacy and security claims can be inspected rather than taken on trust.
  </p>

  <h2>Our content standard</h2>
  <p>
    Guides are written for concrete debugging tasks and include reproducible examples, known limits
    and links to the relevant tool. We consolidate pages when two URLs solve the same job instead of
    publishing search-only variations. Material corrections and safety issues can be reported through
    the contact page.
  </p>

  <h2>Our principles</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Private by design.</strong> Every tool runs entirely in your
      browser. Your text is never sent to or stored on a server.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Free and no sign-up.</strong> No account, no paywall, no install.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Fast and focused.</strong> Each tool does one thing well and loads
      instantly.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we keep it free</h2>
  <p>
    {SITE.name} is supported by unobtrusive advertising. This lets us keep every
    tool free for everyone while covering hosting costs. Read our
    <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> to learn how ads and analytics work.
  </p>

  <h2>Get in touch</h2>
  <p>
    Have feedback or a tool you'd like to see? Visit our
    <a href="/contact">Contact page</a> — we read every message.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
